    <div>
        <h1>How to Upload Video for Training in PhishSims</h1>

        <ol>
            <li>Log in to your PhishSims account using your username and password.</li>
            <li>Once logged in, navigate to the "Training" section of the dashboard.</li>
        <img src="/img/Train1.pngalt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Click on the "Training Video" button within the training section drop down.</li>
        <img src="/img/trainvdo1.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>On the video upload page, Write the Video Name and click on the "Choose File" button to select the video file from your computer.</li>
        <img src="/img/trainvdo2.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Locate the video file on your computer and click "Open" to upload it to PhishSims.</li>
        <img src="/img/trainvdo3.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/trainvdo4.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Click on "Upload" and Wait for the upload process to complete. Depending on the size of the video, this may take some time.</li>
        <img src="/img/trainvdo5.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/TrainingVideo7.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/TrainingVideo8.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>After the upload is successful, you will see a confirmation message indicating that the video has been added to your training library.</li>
        <img src="/img/TrainingVideo9.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>You can now assign the uploaded video to specific training modules or courses within PhishSims.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Make sure to follow any naming conventions or file format requirements specified by PhishSims for video uploads. Additionally, ensure that the video content complies with the acceptable use policy of PhishSims.</p>

